SV_DESCRIPTION: Offers confidential walk-in primary health care services to UBC students. Treats common medical conditions such as gynecological issues, birth control, sexually transmitted diseases, sports injuries, infections, immunization needs and emotional problems. In addition, access to many medical specialists is provided. Specialist clinics actually held in the health service include psychiatry, plastic surgery, dermatology, orthopedics, sports medicine, and ear-nose-throat. Appointments recommended. Call for an appointment, or visit the website for online appointment booking.
HOURS: Mon - Fri, 7:50 a.m. - 4 p.m.; Well-Women exams only Wed, 4 p.m. - 8 p.m. (Sept-April)

Services include primary medical and nursing care, specialty consultation in infectious disease and ophthalmology, methadone maintenance, addictions counselling, diabetes education program, phlebotomy and limited medication dispensing. Clients may or may not have medical coverage, may be receiving income assistance, and/or may be new to Vancouver. Evening clinic hours offered Monday - Thursday. Saturday and Sunday hours also available.

Provides a confidential free health care service for youth 12 to 24 years. Clinic staffed by a doctor, nurse/counsellor, outreach worker and office assistant. Care includes, but is not limited to: blood tests; pap tests; referrals to specialists; and vaccines against viruses like hepatitis. Provides medications including oral contraceptives at cost or free for youth in need. Offers free lab tests: pregnancy and STI tests are always available. Blood testing (e.g. for HIV or hepatitis) is available once a week. The downtown clinic serves primarily youth patients who may be homeless, at-risk, and/or patients with severe mental health and addictions. The James Bay site endeavours to serve primarily health-related and counselling concerns for youth patients. The Yates Street clinic offers evening hours Monday and Wednesday. Michigan Street clinic offers evening hours Tuesday and Thursday.
